nother couple of years before the JT-60SA can sustain plasmas long enough f=
or use in meaningful physics experiments. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64=
, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>That =
said, the success of and learnings from JT-60SA will bolster the progress o=
f ITER, the world's largest and most advanced experimental tokamak reactor.=
 The main goal of ITER is to demonstrate the feasibility of large scale fus=
ion. While ITER is based in France, it&#8217;s one of the largest  </span><=
em>international</em><span> scientific collaborations in history, with over=
 35 countries involved, including the US, China, and Russia. </span></p><p =
style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Both ITER and JT-60SA have been slow &#8212; with such=
