lor: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">Palmer Luckey</a><span>,=
 the founder of Oculus and Anduril. And Palmer thinks AGI, if we achieve it=
, will be more useful on defense than offense. </span></p><blockquote style=
=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b4e9; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>I am not scared of AGI the way that a lot =
of people are. I think that AGI is a technology where the benefits do accru=
e more to the defender than on the offensive side.</em></p><p style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
 margin-left: 20px;"><em>Obviously, people can pick examples here and there=
, &quot;Aw, but here's this horrible thing that it could be used for.&quot;=
 I still think the benefits actually accrue more to the defender&#8230; </e=
m></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>In other words, if AGI is so=
 good that it can come up with anthrax two and it's just an incredibly powe=
rful thing, I would hope that AGI can also come up with a thing that immuni=
zes people against it or that builds nanobots that are in our blood stream =
at all times that are able to, on the fly, compute exactly what they're goi=
ng to do to stop any biological threat, natural or man-made. It's a case wh=
ere the defensive uses like that are actually going to outweigh the offensi=
ve uses in the long run.</em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64=
, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>That&=
